The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 21 February is 39,518 (4,573.9 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 16 February, there were 761 new confirmed cases (88.1 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 09 February, there were 1,226 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 38% (465 fewer cases).
